{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784253000704189609,"compiled_state":{"alias":"immune-floury-toad","assignee":"","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"sshsig","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","envelope":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.opcert.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","head_sha":"b0ac25447203d864463408c933497f21bc1f8dbf","key_id":null,"kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: 3863-a783-b38f-4c8a","material: 6c06e89eda93a97d","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 1","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (b0ac25447)","regver: b293b9a55de591cc","verified-at-sha:79a10387a16d551668c4408716b135376480005f","dep absent .rebar/criteria_routing.json","dep absent .rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md","dep absent tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py"],"material_fingerprint":"6c06e89eda93a97d","merged_log_commit":"79a10387a16d551668c4408716b135376480005f","principal":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","signature":null,"signed_at":1784165987801108000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":1,"unsigned":15},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"b467901c913c49bd26df2373a20f18ccc531289fd42d6d293106145aac308867","event_uuid":"5c74b4be-fdfa-4229-b5e7-232cf7d7caf9","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784253000704189608-5c74b4be-fdfa-4229-b5e7-232cf7d7caf9"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"5c2eef83-9ceb-4320-ad07-f54047bb7399","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Plan-review BLOCK remediated: corrected both nonexistent regression test paths to tests/unit/test_criteria_overlay.py and tests/unit/workflow/test_production_batch_runner.py. Applied the useful advisories by splitting compound ACs, fixing exact prompt front matter and rubric headings/markers as mechanical test oracles, and citing the parent experiment record plus established overlay/fan-in prior art.","timestamp":1784164851188518001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Applied signed-PASS advisories that materially improve the plan: added a Finding threshold AC, enumerated all supported matrix values in the rubric contract, aligned the project-configuration non-finding AC to the exact literal, and split the remaining compound routing/posture AC.","timestamp":1784165506465698001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Retyped from story to task after the final scheduling audit: next-batch intentionally skips childless stories as planning containers. Scope, acceptance criteria, file impact, proving commands, dependencies, and title are unchanged; this ticket is the implementation leaf it was already planned to be.","timestamp":1784169402560236001}],"created_at":1784164041500193001,"deps":[],"description":"## Why\n\nThe epic needs a project-owned Pass 1 finder that rejects concrete portability failures without demanding generic portability prose. The fresh-worktree experiment has already proven that the project overlay, prompt loader, and production fan-in mechanism support this extension shape.\n\n## What\n\nAdd and activate `project.portability` in the project criteria overlay, author its Pass 1 rubric prompt, and add focused integration tests for prompt resolution, scope routing, and production finding fan-in.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- `.rebar/criteria_routing.json`\n- `.rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md`\n- `tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py`\n- Pass 1 discovery for both leaf and container tickets\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Pass 2 validity or impact logic\n- Pass 3 disposition logic\n- coaching moves\n- live semantic calibration\n- remediation of existing portability debt\n\n## Approach\n\nUse the existing project overlay seam rather than adding a built-in criterion. This keeps rebar-specific policy in the rebar repository while exercising the same supported extension boundary available to clients. Configure `exec: 1-TURN`, `facet: project-invariants` (the established free-form project grouping used by `tests/unit/test_criteria_overlay.py`), `applies_at.scope: [container, leaf]`, `default_posture: blocking`, and `block_threshold: 0.9`, then add the id to `activate`.\n\nThe prompt front matter is fixed as:\n\n- `schema_version: 1`\n- `title: Rebar portability`\n- `description: Find concrete rebar portability failures across supported client shapes.`\n- `execution_mode: single_turn`, the prompt-library counterpart of routing `exec: 1-TURN`\n- `category: plan-review-criterion`\n- `dimension: project-invariants`\n\nThe rubric body uses these exact second-level headings so tests have a mechanical oracle:\n\n- `## Finding threshold`\n- `## Required finding fields`\n- `## Supported client-shape matrix`\n- `## Non-findings`\n\nUnder `Finding threshold`, require all four counterexample elements before emitting a finding: cited plan mechanism, materially different supported client shape, causal failure mechanism, and observable breakage scenario.\n\nUnder `Required finding fields`, specify `location: str` for the plan citation, `finding: str` for the assumption plus causal mechanism, `scenarios: list[str]` for the alternate client shape plus observable breakage, `evidence: list[str]` for the plan quote plus grounding facts, and `criteria: list[str]` containing `project.portability`.\n\nUnder `Supported client-shape matrix`, include these exact labels and values:\n\n- `Harness`: Python library, CLI, remote MCP; no Claude Code or Codex dependency.\n- `Target project`: Ruby, Python, Java, Next.js, .NET, Terraform subprojects in a monorepo.\n- `Platform and venue`: macOS, Windows, Linux, BSD, CI, servers, developer workstations.\n- `Project location and access`: in-checkout current working directory, explicitly located workspace, server outside the checkout, no unrestricted-local-filesystem assumption.\n\nUnder `Non-findings`, require the literal rules `Silence about portability is not a finding` and `Project-specific behavior behind project configuration or an explicit extension boundary is allowed`.\n\n## Grounding\n\nPrior art is `tests/unit/test_criteria_overlay.py`, which proves the overlay and prompt contract, plus `tests/unit/workflow/test_production_batch_runner.py`, which covers the real fan-in runner. The parent epic `jira-reb-1003` records the completed experiment at `2026-07-16T00:50:08Z`: worktree `/Users/joeoakhart/rebar-jira-reb-1003-portability`, branch `experiment/jira-reb-1003-portability`, base `b0ac25447203d864463408c933497f21bc1f8dbf`, result `experiment=PASS; routed_scopes={container:true,leaf:true}; project_fan_in=[project.portability]; surfaced_findings=1; move_loaded=project-portability; restricted_to=project.portability`.\n\n## Test Strategy\n\nExercise the real overlay loader, prompt resolver, routing registry, and `ProductionBatchRunner` fan-in with deterministic fakes. Tests inspect the authored rubric contract; live LLM behavior belongs to the calibration child.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The overlay activates `project.portability` with `exec: 1-TURN`, `facet: project-invariants`, and `applies_at.scope: [container, leaf]`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k criterion_activation`.\n- [ ] The activated criterion uses `default_posture: blocking` plus `block_threshold: 0.9`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k criterion_activation`.\n- [ ] The project rubric declares the exact six front-matter values specified in this plan. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k prompt_frontmatter`.\n- [ ] The project rubric resolves through the production prompt loader for `project.portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k prompt_resolution`.\n- [ ] A leaf plan routes `project.portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k leaf_routing`.\n- [ ] A container plan routes `project.portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k container_routing`.\n- [ ] Production project fan-in surfaces an injected `project.portability` finding. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k production_fan_in`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains the exact `Finding threshold` heading plus all four counterexample elements. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k finding_threshold`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains the exact `Required finding fields` heading plus the five typed field markers specified in this plan. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k finding_schema_markers`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains every label-value pair specified under `Supported client-shape matrix`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k client_shape_matrix`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains the exact rule `Silence about portability is not a finding`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k omission_guard`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains the exact rule `Project-specific behavior behind project configuration or an explicit extension boundary is allowed`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k project_configuration_guard`.\n- [ ] Existing behavior remains unchanged when the project overlay is absent. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_criteria_overlay.py tests/unit/workflow/test_production_batch_runner.py`.\n","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":".rebar/criteria_routing.json","reason":"activate and route project.portability"},{"path":".rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md","reason":"author the Pass 1 portability rubric"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py","reason":"verify project criterion integration and boundaries"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","jira-reb-1003"]],"parent_id":"jira-reb-1003","parent_status_uuid":"1ca94ed4-93fe-4066-ab41-437e21e9e6b0","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["plan-review","portability","project-criteria"],"ticket_id":"3863-a783-b38f-4c8a","ticket_type":"task","title":"Activate the rebar portability finder","verify_commands":[{"command":".venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py","dd_id":"DD-1","dd_text":"Project criterion integration is covered"},{"command":".venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_criteria_overlay.py tests/unit/workflow/test_production_batch_runner.py","dd_id":"DD-2","dd_text":"Overlay absence and production fan-in remain compatible"}]},"source_event_uuids":["43c14435-4fea-4e96-b08f-4d7cd1ee1ffb","b60761d7-f498-4cba-99b2-828f1c0b6a87","301d650a-be37-4b8f-8992-712961067262","aa193276-f5c0-49b7-9d17-58ca5c74e6d8","2ba9f477-7dbf-4ac3-aa75-94f4f994687c","29b1da69-f15c-4b47-a9d9-9c93c5cb1729","f63b9736-fe58-47bb-8a39-ab97f45dcf50","0b9e4fb7-6d2c-4850-9a12-d468518eab89","510e25cf-9202-43df-9c3b-94e566a8924f","7a93b6e6-fafe-4bad-8820-f9dafd13f6d8","3aa3248e-66a3-4042-809e-8e130be124d1","cbd3a920-47ec-42b4-80ad-0f46465ad743","ebad1f47-7080-4edb-abd6-117be965ba07","1ca94ed4-93fe-4066-ab41-437e21e9e6b0","23a585eb-580b-43d2-b4a5-934c87f9b5c9","5c74b4be-fdfa-4229-b5e7-232cf7d7caf9"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784253000704189609,"uuid":"9e3aa971-06db-4728-a524-29f8afa05b94"}